  "summary": "Reverse shell to hardcoded internal IP on library use",
  "details": "internallib_v234 exports a function that shells out via `/bin/bash -c` and pipes a remote script fetched with curl from reverse-shell.sh into `sh`, targeting the hardcoded RFC1918 address 10.0.74.133:443. Any consumer that calls the exported `command()` triggers an outbound interactive shell from the installer's host to that endpoint, giving the operator of that address a backdoor on the caller's machine. The package also declares itself as its own dependency and ships a CI config pointing npm at a local registry (0.0.0.0:4873), consistent with a dependency-confusion payload targeting an internal package name.",
